revisions.description: o Added Notifications for PDU devices (power on/off). o Added lgpEventParameters branch for defining notification payload that specifically identifies objects that are contained in tables. o Added new varbind to the lgpEventConditionEntryAdded and lgpEventConditionEntryRemoved notifications. o Fixed minor SMIv2 warnings and issues

o Added Notifications for PDU devices (power on/off). o Added lgpEventParameters branch for defining notification payload that specifically identifies objects that are contained in tables. o Added new varbind to the lgpEventConditionEntryAdded and lgpEventConditionEntryRemoved notifications. o Fixed minor SMIv2 warnings and issues
Modified contact email address and deprecated both: o lgpEventAgentFirmwareUpdateSuccessful o lgpEventAgentFirmwareCorrupt which were moved to the LIEBERT-GP-AGENT-MIB document.
Added events for firmware update successful and for firmware corrupt.
Added support for Liebert DS Unit.

lgpEventParameters.name: lgpEventParameters
lgpEventParameters.description: This sub tree describes various parameters/data that are carried in the payload of some notifications.

lgpEventParmTableRef.name: lgpEventParmTableRef
lgpEventParmTableRef.description: This object will be included as a varbind in some lgpEventNotifications. It is a reference to a table object in the MIB. The value of this object will be the OID of a table that the object that the notification applies to is defined. The notification containing this object will also contain a varbind 'lgpEventParmTableRowRef' that will specify which instance (row) in the table the object is defined in. Example: NOTIFICATION: lgpEventConditionEntryAdded varbind: lgpConditionId 6 varbind: lgpConditionDescr lgpConditionRcpBranchBreakerOpen varbind: lgpConditionTime 393884848 varbind: lgpEventParmTableRef lgpPduRbTable varbind: lgpEventParmTableRowRef lgpPduRbEntryId.1.4 In the above example the breaker opened for a Receptacle branch. The specific receptacle branch is specified by the additional varbind (lgpEventParmTableRowRef). In this case the notification is for the 4th receptacle branch on the 1st PDU in the PDU cluster.

lgpEventParmTableRowRef.name: lgpEventParmTableRowRef
lgpEventParmTableRowRef.description: This is a reference to the intersection of a row and column (cell) in the table specified by the companion varbind (lgpEventParmTableRef) in this notification. The row in the table where this cell exists represents the object that this notification applies to. Example: NOTIFICATION: lgpEventRcpPowerStateChangeOff varbind: sysUpTime 393885975 varbind: lgpEventParmTableRef lgpPduRcpTable varbind: lgpEventParmTableRowRef lgpPduRcpEntryId.2.4.5 In the above example the power state changed for a Receptacle. The table containing the definition of the receptacle (lgpPduRcpTable) is given by the varbind (lgpEventParmTableRef) The specific receptacle is specified by the varbind (lgpEventParmTableRowRef). In this case the notification is for the 5th receptacle on the 4th receptacle branch on the 2nd PDU in the PDU cluster. If one wanted to retrieve the user assigned label for this receptacle the OID would be: lgpPduRcpEntryUsrLabel.2.4.5

lgpEventConditionEntryAdded.name: lgpEventConditionEntryAdded
lgpEventConditionEntryAdded.description: This notification is sent each time a condition is inserted into the conditions table.

lgpEventConditionEntryRemoved.name: lgpEventConditionEntryRemoved
lgpEventConditionEntryRemoved.description: This notification is sent each time a condition is removed from the conditions table.

lgpEventLowBatteryWarning.name: lgpEventLowBatteryWarning
lgpEventLowBatteryWarning.description: The battery's remaining charge is less than or equal to the agent's configured low threshold 'lgpPwrConfigLowBatteryWarningTime'.

lgpEventLoadTransferedToBypass.name: lgpEventLoadTransferedToBypass
lgpEventLoadTransferedToBypass.description: The device has transferred the load to the bypass source.

lgpEventInternalFault.name: lgpEventInternalFault
lgpEventInternalFault.description: The device has reported an internal fault.

lgpEventBatteryTestFailed.name: lgpEventBatteryTestFailed
lgpEventBatteryTestFailed.description: The device has reported a battery self-test failure.

lgpEventOutputOverload.name: lgpEventOutputOverload
lgpEventOutputOverload.description: The device has reported an output overload condition.

lgpEventEstablishedPowerRedundancy.name: lgpEventEstablishedPowerRedundancy
lgpEventEstablishedPowerRedundancy.description: The device has transitioned to the user defined redundant state.

lgpEventLostPowerRedundancy.name: lgpEventLostPowerRedundancy
lgpEventLostPowerRedundancy.description: The device as transitioned to a non-redundant power state as defined by the user configured threshold.

lgpEventAgentFirmwareUpdateSuccessful.name: lgpEventAgentFirmwareUpdateSuccessful
lgpEventAgentFirmwareUpdateSuccessful.description: The firmware update to the agent card has completed successfully. This element has been relocated to lgpAgentFirmwareUpdateSuccessful in the LIEBERT-GP-AGENT-MIB document.

lgpEventAgentFirmwareCorrupt.name: lgpEventAgentFirmwareCorrupt
lgpEventAgentFirmwareCorrupt.description: The firmware update to the agent card has failed and the firmware is now corrupt. This element has been relocated to lgpAgentFirmwareCorrupt in the LIEBERT-GP-AGENT-MIB document.

lgpEventConfigModified.name: lgpEventConfigModified
lgpEventConfigModified.description: Configuration for the referenced PDU has been modified.

lgpEventModuleAdded.name: lgpEventModuleAdded
lgpEventModuleAdded.description: A hot-swappable module has been added to the object specified by the lgpEventParmTableRef and lgpEventParmTableRowRef.

lgpEventModuleRemoved.name: lgpEventModuleRemoved
lgpEventModuleRemoved.description: A hot-swappable module has been removed from the object specified by the lgpEventParmTableRef and lgpEventParmTableRowRef.

lgpEventRcpPowerStateChangeOn.name: lgpEventRcpPowerStateChangeOn
lgpEventRcpPowerStateChangeOn.description: Receptacle's power state has been changed from OFF to ON.

lgpEventRcpPowerStateChangeOff.name: lgpEventRcpPowerStateChangeOff
lgpEventRcpPowerStateChangeOff.description: Receptacle's power state has been changed from ON to OFF.

lgpEventRcpLoadAdded.name: lgpEventRcpLoadAdded
lgpEventRcpLoadAdded.description: The receptacle's load started drawing power. This notification is asserted when the receptacle power is ON and the associated load was previously not drawing power but is now drawing power. This event is not asserted as a result of turning the receptacle power ON.

lgpEventRcpLoadRemoved.name: lgpEventRcpLoadRemoved
lgpEventRcpLoadRemoved.description: The receptacle's load stopped drawing power. This notification is asserted when the receptacle power is ON and the associated load was previously drawing power but is now no longer drawing power. This event is not asserted as a result of turning the receptacle power OFF.
